:: CREATE CHANNELS ::

Click on Channels
Click on Manage Software Channels
Click on Manage Repositories
Click on Create New Repository

:Create new repositories as follows:

CentOS 5 x86_64
Repository Label - CentOS5-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/5/os/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - CentOS5-x86_64-Updates
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/5/updates/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

CentOS 6 x86_64
Repository Label - CentOS6-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/6/os/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - CentOS6-x86_64-Updates
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/6/updates/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - spacewalk-client-rhel6-x86_64
Repository URL - http://spacewalk.redhat.com/yum/1.8/RHEL/6/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

RHEL 6 x86_64
Repository Label - RHEL6-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://local-rhn-mirror.domain
Then click on Create Repository